# NATS Integration

Design docs: `docs/ADR/09-sse-streaming-and-nats.md`, `docs/NATS_CONVENTIONS.md`

## Subject naming

- `federation.deliver.{activityType}` — JetStream, durable delivery queue
- `federation.dlq.{activityType}` — JetStream, dead-letter queue
- `events.public` / `events.public.local` / `events.user.{accountID}` / `events.hashtag.{tag}` — core pub/sub, ephemeral SSE fan-out

## Conventions

- Stream names: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (`FEDERATION`, `FEDERATION_DLQ`).
- Consumer names: lower-kebab-case (`federation-worker`).
- All streams created via `EnsureStreams` in `internal/nats/streams.go` at startup.
- SSE events use `SSEEvent` struct with pre-serialized JSON `Data` field — no re-serialization in the Hub.
- Hub subscribes to NATS subjects on demand (when SSE client connects) and unsubscribes when last client disconnects.
